import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['precipitation'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temperature'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("How does the temperature vary throughout the year in Seattle?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
